US.Jobs Jobs - via XML

As of 12:01 AM ET, May 17th, the urls which these feeds are served from (xmlfeed.us.jobs, xmlfeed.jobcentral.com, feeds.us.jobs) will cease to serve content, and will begin redirecting to a new url, accessible only from https, that requires you submit some information to acquire an authorization code (which must be appended as a query string to all future requests), as well as agree to a set of terms and conditions. The new url, xmlfeed.directemployers.org is live now, and we would encourage you to acquire your code, and make whatever alterations necessary ahead of time to avoid breaking on the morning of May 17th.


Should you want to revoke consent to the terms and conditions and have the information you submitted deleted, please contact feeds@directemployers.org with your request.
